The paper deals with a path planning problem, which is a common topic in robotics and automation. The use of meta-heuristic approaches suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approximation algorithm, which falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The empirical evaluation of the proposed method suggests that it performs better than a state-of-the-art method, which indicates that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the problem of subpath planning can be seen as a problem of optimization, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Systems and Control) sub-category.
